    "finalText": "I can’t answer that reliably from what I pulled.\n\nThe data source I hit came back with **project 0 / no scoped project data**, so there’s no real change-order exposure in that result. To answer your question correctly, I need to scope it one of two ways:\n\n- **One project**: “Vermillion Rise” / “Eye Surgeons” / etc.\n- **Portfolio-wide**: all active projects\n\nWhat you’re asking for, specifically, is the gap between:\n- **work performed or costs incurred**\nand\n- **approved owner change-order dollars / billable CO money**\n\nThat usually shows up in a few buckets:\n- **Open change events** not yet turned into priced COs\n- **Pending prime change orders** not yet approved by the owner\n- **Executed field work tied to unsigned CO backup**\n- **Cost hits already in the job** with no matching owner-side recovery yet\n\nIf you want, I can do this **portfolio-wide** and give you:\n1. the biggest unbilled exposure by project,  \n2. what portion is **pending approval** vs **not formally submitted**, and  \n3. where we’ve likely already done the work without paper in place."
